description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Practice Nurse Post &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Part Time 20-24 hrs &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lister House&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Who we are:- &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lister House has 4 sites and over 35,000 patients spread across the city of Derby, this may make us a substantial practice but we still maintain a personal approach to patient centred care. We refuse to be a faceless institution.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have a strong nursing team of 19 each offering a varied skill mix and although a large group we work as a closely knit supportive team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer&lt;/strong&gt;:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong GP &amp; ACP support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GP &amp; student nurse training practice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive reward structure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Innovative guidelines for appointment bookings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Modern purpose built premises&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal applicant will be&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A highly motivated practice nurse who is:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Patient focussed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Has a strong team work ethic&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Ideally be skilled in chronic disease management, telephone triage, travel health, cytology screening, wound care management and childhood immunisations. Minor illness experience would also be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Be flexible around working hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hold a full clean driving licence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a practice with a strong training culture and like to invest in our staff.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like to discuss before application please contact Sharon Griffin – Nurse Manager.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date for applications 7th December 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview date planned 17th December &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
